snippet.textDisplay:
According to two separate witnesses on the ground nearby, the helicopter was "struggling" and "in distress" just before impact.
This indicates to me that:
1. There was a mechanical/electrical malfunction, which is highly unlikely based on the S-76's remarkable safety record
or
2.
Before the crash and because of poor visibility, the pilot accidentally
clipped something that affected the chopper's airworthiness

Irregardless,
unless there was an equipment failure, the pilot is/was solely
responsible for having made the decision to fly in such extreme
conditions. He broke a fundamental rule found on page one of every
aviation manual ever printed.

Kobe and everyone else on board had so much more to give.
I just hope the press shows common respect and decency to the families.

snippet.textDisplay: Quick fast death,  Not knowing you’re dying    the best kind of death,,,      most people won’t get that kind of death.  A natural death is slow and it isn’t for the faint of heart,,,   I was with my mother when she slowly died from cancer three weeks to die in and out of consciousness body failing Organs shutting down blindness at the end,  bones breaking yeah it’s not a thing you want to  Witness ,but I was proud to be there for her ,proud to be her son..  but now I’m suffering from it thinking of death on a daily basis .Sometimes hourly basis. with no one in my life... no one to call my own ,,just me and my dog which was her dog..    On top of that homeless       all  going on 3 years now..     Last word she said to me ....I will miss you,likecrazy   ,,,,  I don’t want to leave...      My father died almost the same way ,,,   dragged out . I wasnt in there the time of his death I was in the next room ,,,,with my mom ,,I made sure I was there siting next to her but you knew something was gonna happen that day or all you can do is give her major pain medications so drugged up ,,she probably doesn’t know anything..     Then her breathing  got shallow and slower..    then she  took one more breath and stopped...     my  cousins   husband     10 years younger then my mom   died  the before her

(Ezekiel 3:6-7 & 3:11 & 3:16-21): God sends Prophet Ezekiel to warn Israel, even though they won’t listen to God, at least their blood will be off their hands and now they have been warned.
(Galatians 1:10): We are not to care what men think of us, only what God thinks of us and that we do his will and not mans.
(James 5:19-20): Turns a brother or sister in Christ away from their sinning against God.
(Matthew 7:13-14): According to Jesus, most people are heading to Hell, but it will be their doing and not Gods. For God had to go through a gruesome death for us all.
(Matthew 5:29-30): Get the Sin out of your life.
(Matthew 13:18:23): The parable of the sower of the seed/ God’s word on people’s hearts.
(2 Corinthians 10:5): Take your thoughts captive to the obedience of Christ Jesus that come from the enemy. (I say out loud or in my mind, “I rebuke that thought in Jesus name and I cover it with the blood of the Lamb.” Then those thoughts instantly go away.
The spiritual battles first take place in our minds and thoughts and we have a choice to entertain them or not. For an example, if a good-looking man or woman crosses our paths, are we have a choice to lust after that person or are we going to take those evil thoughts captive to the obedience of Christ Jesus and rebuke all wicked thoughts. And Jesus said, “If you lust after that person, you have committed adultery with them in your heart.” (Matthew 5:27-28).
And those who do such things, will not inherit the kingdom of God. (1 Corinthians 6:9-11).
And Jesus said in John 14:15 and John 14:21, “If you love me Keep my commandments.”
(1 John 4:19): We will love Jesus by keeping his commandments, because he first loved us by dying for us all on that bloody cross, so we would not suffer in Hell Fire.
(1 Corinthians 2:9): God will give you your heart’s desire, if you love him by keeping his commandments.
(1 John 5:3): This is how we love God.
(John 15:10): We have to stay in Jesus love, just like Jesus had to stay in the father’s love, by keeping his commandments.
(Ecclesiastes 12:13-14): This is the whole duty of man.
(1 John 2:3-4): This is how we know Jesus, by keeping his commandments and those who don’t keep his commandments are liars and the truth is not in them.
(Romans 11:22): We have to continue in God’s goodness or we will be cut off.
(Isaiah 1:16-17): Put away the evil of your doings.
(Matthew 25:1-13 & 7: 21-23): The foolish virgins who ate and drank with the world and did not have the Holy Spirit inside of them/Oil in their lamps.
(Romans 6:12-16): Don’t use your bodies to sin.
(Galatians 5:16): Walk according to the spirit.
(Romans 8:5-8): To be carnally minded is to be at enmity with God.
(Hebrews 1:9): You have to hate sin, so then God will provide you with his Holy Spirit of promise above everybody else.
(1 Corinthians 2:15-16): A spiritual man judges all things, because he is spiritual and has the Holy Spirit indwelling inside of him.
(Acts 5:32): God only provides those with the Holy Spirit, who OBEY him only. His Holy Spirit will not be in those who practice sin and have a dirty temple/vessel/body, where evil dwells.
(This is why it is very crucial that you mind the things that you watch on television/ tel a vison, and what you hear in your ears, as music goes, because it will affect your heart and the Holy Spirit that is living inside of you).
(1 John 1:9): Confess our Sins to Jesus.
(Proverbs 28:13): Confess and forsake our sins.
(1 John 2:1): We have an advocate with the Father (((IF))) we sin and not when we sin saying, Sin will not be the practice in our lives. The exception and not the rule.
(Romans 6:1-2): We will not continue to sin.
(1 John 3:9): The Holy Spirit with in us, will not let us sin, because we have been born of God.
(John 3:3): We must be born again from above, with the Holy Spirit, to inherit the kingdom of God.
(John 8:11): Jesus tells the woman caught in adultery to go and sin no more.
(Isaiah 59:1) & (John 9:31): God’s word says to us, that he will not hear the prayers of sinners.
(Psalms 34:17) & (Proverbs 15:29) & (James 5:16): God hears and saves the righteous ones.
(James 4:8-9): Come near to God and wash yourselves of sin.
(James 4:7): Come near to God and resist the devil and he will flee from you.
(2 Corinthians 6:14): We are not to be friends with sinners.
(1 Corinthians 5:11): We are not even supposed to eat and associate ourselves with sinners.
(Luke 13:3 & Luke 13:5 & Revelation 3:19): We have to Repent of our sins according to Jesus.
(Revelation 3:16): Jesus said, if you are a Luke warm Christian, one foot in the world and one foot with him, he will spew you out of his mouth.
(Luke 9:23): If you are going to be with Jesus, you have to deny your flesh and follow him and not this world and its corrupted things. Store up treasure in heaven and not on this earth, where you can’t take anything with you. As it says in Matthew 6:19-20.
(Revelation 3:4-5): Those who overcome sin will be worthy.
(Revelation 3:10-11): The wise virgins will not be here to face the Anti-Christ, only the foolish virgins will be, who are going to have to die to gain the fathers kingdom. Their heads will be cut off as it says in Revelation 6:9-11 & Revelation 7:14 & Revelation 20:4.
(Matthew 22:36-40): The two greatest commandments that sum up the 10 according to Jesus.
(Ephesians 6:12): Remember, we wrestle not against flesh and blood.
(Ephesians 6:13-18): Put ye on the full armor of God, to destroy the devil and his evil demons and is schemes.
LET THE BATTLE BEGIN!!!
